Police and Cape Town CCID security outside the cellphone shop. (Lerato Maduna, Netwerk24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - Members of the public responded quickly when they nabbed three men who had robbed a cellphone shop in Cape Town CBD during lunch on Monday.The incident occurred at about 13:30 when the men, wearing police uniforms and brandishing firearms, entered Shezaad Mohamad&rsquo;s shop on Strand Street, demanding cellphones and money, reported Netwerk24.Mohamad said it was members of the public who came to his aid and caught the robbers and police only arrived on scene about an hour afterwards.Police spokesperson Tembinkosi Kinana said police found two cellphones, a gun and ammunition in the suspects&rsquo; possession, reported Sapa.No one was hurt in the robbery.A fourth suspect managed to escape in a white Toyota Etios. The three suspects will appear in the Cape Town Magistrate&rsquo;s Court.See this video taken just after the robbery:&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.